body:
@animosity22 Thanks for clearing up why this happened.

Is this mentioned anywhere in the docs? If so I must have missed it. The `purge` documentation only mentions `remote:path` which suggests that it would actually check whether I'm working against a configured remote. The documentation also mentions `source:sourcePath` in other cases in which case this behavior seems a bit misleading?

I will add a comment to the issue that you linked, thanks a lot. Feel free to close this issue if you see this as expected behavior.
